----------------------: Hard Link vs Soft Link :--------------------------------------
Inode values:
 - Unique number for every file in linux , contains metadata. 

Create and Manage Hard Links 
 - ln <target_file> <link_file>
 - ln demo.txt Hlink
 - links to files only not folders. 
 - Can access the data from hardlink
 - inode number is similar to the actual file.
Note
 - We can use copy cmd, i.e., cp but if we modify the actual file it won't impact the actual file, but in Hlink it's viceversa. 

Create and Manage Soft Links 
 - ln -s <target_file> <helloshortcut.txt>
 - ln -s demo.txt Slink
 - readlink helloshortcut.txt
 - soft links to files, folders, diff-files systems as well.
 - Can't access the data from Slink, only stores the path.

--------------------: FILE PERMISSIONS / SECURITY "chmod" :-------------------------
read, r - 4
write, w - 2
execute, x - 1
no permission - 0

Initials: owners, group, others
 - chmod 421 demo.txt / chmod 777 demo.txt

chattr +i demo.txt - Immutable files/ config/ imp files
chattr -i demo.txt - Mutable

u - users
g - groups
o - others
+ - grant permission
_ - revoke permission
= - grant a special permission & revoke other permission

Ex:
 - chmod +x demo.txt - users grant execute permission.

